author: @pandalandalopalis6515
text:
I love Vernon and see where he was going with the caramel popcorn = sticky fingers point, but caramel popcorn is actually the one popcorn that doesn't leave residue on your hands. Unless it's different in Korea, when I have caramel popcorn it's a dried caramel coating and not actively liquid or sticky. It's kind of like a shell and because it's dry, it doesn't leave caramel residue on your fingers. Whereas generally every other type of popcorn will leave some kind of residue on your hands (be it salt, butter, savory, white cheddar, etc.)
Anyway the debate is not meant to be logical hahaha but I'm surprised the caramel team didn't counter with this point

author: @ayuannur9557
text:
Our Logic and Debate Ace, Moon Junhui. 

Fly Carats to the moon
Let Carats play among the stars
Let Carats see what spring is like
On a, Jupiter and Mars


Hopefully it won't be burden for you if ever there's the next debate night. I don't want Jun to feel burden. But also, just like other Carats, I feel so much proud and happy that Jun being polite, well mannered, never mocked other members, showing how he always remembers Carats, applaud or nod when he's in agreement with other member, and asked Wonwoo politely while patiently waiting for his turn to talk. You know, these really shows the quality of someone's personality. So proud for always stan for you! 

Though, I kinda a little bit feeling bad. Especially when other Carats pointed out that sarcastically that Jun only using the "Carat" card. The first one is great, the next one is great too, but feel kinda weak since Jun using the same reasoning again: Carat. 
But screw my high expectations. Knowing Jun being Seventeen Jun always remember Carat is enough for my heart.

author: @beilinyi328
text:
Hi everyone, you all want to know
I'm actually a new CARAT
at first the bias was Minghao (THE 8), but the longer I got to know and look at SEVENTEEN, my bias changed from Minghao to Jun and until now I really like Jun. I tried looking at all of Seventeen’s videos and was definitely looking for Jun. From concert videos, Inside Seventeen, Going Seventeen as well as videos from YouTube. But I’m a little sad because if you’re all looking for Jun -related videos, the quantity is very little. I also like to find comments from CARAT or Non-Carat about June because since I got to know June. I found him to be a human being who needed to be protected because he was a very good person, indeed many saw him as a quiet person but in fact he was a friendly person and talked a lot. this is because I watched her videos related to Chinese programs or interviews, she was very confident and very happy. Also, I once read from one of the websites or watched a video i.e. member Minghao once said that Jun told him about the difficulty of speaking in Korean, so Jun expressed through deeds. Mingyu also once said that Jun looks quiet but in fact he is a caring person in silence and in fact I can see his concern for his members as well as others. if you all pay close attention, you will all be able to see the thing. But now more and more, he is a little brave and has the confidence to stand out and speak properly with the help of members and he tries to interact with us (CARAT). Actually the main point I want to say is that I feel very happy because this is the first time I see Jun’s name a lot in the comment space. because usually when I see any video related to Seventeen, I’ll look for Jun’s name. And I find that very rarely people comment on Jun and there are some videos, there is no Jun's name at all. I feel very sad because many do not see the real Jun. In conclusion, this video is my favorite for now, because just an hour into this video was uploaded already a lot of June names. (there were 60 comments out of 2,749 mentioning June’s name).
I am very, very happy. I hope Jun will have high confidence to talk more
as well as I hope you all can see Jun from the other side.
forgive me for not being good at speaking English

I love you all
I love Seventeen
I love JUN


Moonranghae
Junranghae
Huiranghae

author: @danielaclovarts5312
text:
우리 정한이가 카라멜맛 팝콘 고른 기념으로 정한이의 무논리를 보태줄 무논리논리 한마디 하고 갑니다😊

카라멜 팝콘이야 말로 이 토론의 당연한 승자입니다. 카라멜 팝콘은 고소한 맛 팝콘을 포함하고 있기 때문이죠. 

잘 생각해 보십시오. 카라멜 팝콘엔 카라멜 맛만 있느냐하면 그건 아닙니다. 카라멜 팝콘에도 어느정도 소금간을 합니다. 또한 모든 팝콘 개체에 카라멜이 완벽하게 도포되는 것도 아니죠. 몇몇 개체는 카라멜 옷을 덜 입습니다. 그래서 결국은 고소한 맛과 다를 바 없는 개체가 탄생하기도 하죠. 

하지만 이것은 반대로 생각하면, 카라멜 팝콘을 먹음으로서 우리는 카라멜 맛 팝콘과 고소한 맛 팝콘의 조화와 상생, 다양성의 보존을 이뤄낼 수 있다는 얘기이기도 합니다. 고소한 맛 하나로 팝콘계를 통일하려는 시도는 지극히 전체주의적이며 구시대적인 압박이 아닐 수 없습니다.

어떤 팝콘전통주의자들은 고소한 맛 외의 팝콘을 팝콘으로 인정하지 않는다고 들었습니다. 그러나  우리가 전통으로 여기는 모든 문화와 유산 또한 시대의 요구에 맞게 변화된 결과임을 잊지 말아야 할 것입니다. 그렇기에 팝콘전통주의자 분들이 카라멜 맛 팝콘으로의 시대적 이양을 거부하지 않길 간곡히 바랍니다.

카라멜 맛 팝콘은 고소한 맛 팝콘의 입지를 계승하여 이미 팝콘 사회의 주류로 자리잡았습니다. 언젠가는 치즈나 갈릭 맛 팝콘에게 자리를 물려줄 지도 모릅니다. 그러나 그 또한 일어난다면 받아들여야 할 일입니다. 왜냐하면, 무엇보다 중요한 것은 팝콘 사회가 항상 활짝 핀 팝콘처럼 열린 마음을 유지하는 것이기 때문입니다. 우리는 시대적 흐름을 무시하고 팝콘기계 안에 남은 옥수수 껍데기처럼 고이지 않아야 하겠습니다.

짙은 갈색으로 반들반들하게 코팅된, 뜨겁고 바삭한 카라멜 맛 팝콘과 그 사이 하얀 보석처럼 박혀있는 덜 코팅된 팝콘-고소한 맛 팝콘의 유지를 잇는-을 떠올려 보십시오. 그 아름다운 밸런스와 환상적인 맛의 하모니야말로 우리가 추구해야 할 팝콘의 미래인 것입니다!

우리 같이 외칩시다! 팝콘 포 프라임 라이프!👏👏
